Business Brief -- Vital Signs Inc.:
   Company Agrees to Acquire
   Biomedical Dynamics Corp.
The companies said approximately 1.7 million shares of
Vital Signs' common stock will be issuable under the proposed
transaction, based on an average price of Vital Signs' common
stock of between $20.875 and $26 a share in national
over-the-counter trading. The proposed transaction, which is
subject to shareholder approval and other conditions, is
expected to close in March or April.
   Vital Signs of Totowa, N.J., makes medical products for
anesthesia, respiratory and related critical care
applications. Biomedical Dynamics makes medical devices for
critical patient care. The companies couldn't be reached for
elaboration.